  "response": "Yes, money laundering is definitely illegal. It is a criminal activity that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. The goal is to make the money appear as if it comes from legitimate sources.\n\nMoney laundering is considered a serious crime because it allows criminals to profit from illegal activities such as drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, and organized crime, while also undermining the integrity of financial systems. Laws against money laundering exist in virtually every country, and those who are caught engaging in it can face severe penalties, including hefty fines and long prison sentences. International organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) work to set global standards and promote effective measures to combat money laundering and terrorist financing.",
